heaviest_rainfall.status: The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm fell at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour over the 37.2 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: On 02 September 2025, the rain fell at an exceptional rate, peaking at 27.0mm per hour, the heaviest downpour recorded.  A total of 21.19mm fell over the 15.0 hour storm.

longest_rain.status: A storm today ranked 9th for the longest continuous rainfall according to our records, lasting a total of18.1 hours.  It came with 5.59mm of rainfall, at times, falling at {this_max}mm per hour.  Rain fell for 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 36.8mm with a maximum intensity of 4.6mm per hour.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 5.2°C) and outside temperature (down 3.9°C) and drier conditions in outside humidity (down 6%) and rainfall (down 0.2 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in light levels (up 3032 lux), pressure (up 8 mbar), and rainfall (up 0.2 mm).

The past week and month had observable variation in light levels (up 9211 lux), rainfall (down 0.3 mm), and cloud levels (up 617 m) when compared to today.
